The paper deals with a variant of propositional logic that is related to data analysis and association rules, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of linear programming duality to characterize entailment also suggests a connection to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The study of redundancy among partial implications and the definition of a confidence threshold are also relevant to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the use of conditional probabilities and association rules suggests a connection to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
